# Folder Organization Standards

## Feature-based organization

- Organize by **feature** or **route**, not only by technical layer.
- Group related UI under **`src/feature/`**, **`src/pages/`**, or **`src/shared/`** as already used in this repo.

## Component organization

- Each component that has tests/stories/docs lives in its **own folder** when complexity warrants it.
- Apply **YAGNI**: avoid deep nesting for components that are only used together in one place.
- Use **`components/`** for sub-components. Prefer consistent names over `containers` / `presenters` unless the codebase already uses a pattern locally.
- Typical shape:

```
ComponentName/
├── ComponentName.tsx
├── ComponentName.test.tsx
├── ComponentName.stories.tsx
├── ComponentName.module.scss
└── components/
    └── SubComponent/
        ├── SubComponent.tsx
        ├── SubComponent.test.tsx
        └── SubComponent.stories.tsx
```

## Tests

- Co-locate **`*.test.tsx`** / **`*.test.ts`** next to sources.
- Storybook specs live in **`.stories.tsx`** alongside components.

## Naming

- **PascalCase** — components and their folders.
- **camelCase** — utilities (**utility-naming-conventions.mdc**).
- **kebab-case** — config files where the repo already does so.

## Imports

- Prefer **aliases** (`utils/`, `types/`, etc.) for cross-folder imports (**import-path-optimization.mdc**).
- Short **relative** imports only inside the same feature folder.

## Constants and maps

- Put **`Record<Enum, …>`** registries and static maps in **`*.constant.ts`** or dedicated modules — see **code-standard.mdc** and **component-injection-map.mdc**.

## Types

- **`*.type.ts`** for shared interfaces/types; co-locate when only one component uses them.

## Documentation

- Prefer **`src/docs/**/*.mdx`**, co-located **`.mdx`** next to components (as in **Inbox**), or a small **`README.md`** in the feature folder — see **generic.mdc** and **mdx-generic.mdc**.

## YAGNI

- Do not add barrels **`index.ts`** unless needed for lazy loading or multi-export boundaries (**performance-architecture-standards.mdc**).

## Example (this codebase)

The **Inbox** feature uses colocated utils, components, and tests under **`src/feature/Inbox/`** — same idea: keep feature work discoverable in one subtree.
